Forge — Asymbl Internal Notice
================================

This repository is a fork of Multica (github.com/multica-ai/multica),
published at github.com/shivasymbl/forge.

Upstream license
----------------
The upstream Multica project is distributed under a modified Apache
License 2.0. The full text is preserved in `LICENSE` (unchanged).

Two relevant restrictions from the upstream license apply to this fork:

1. Hosted/embedded service restriction (§1.a):
   Cannot offer Multica/Forge as a hosted service to third parties or
   embed it in a product sold to third parties without a commercial
   license from Multica, Inc.

   *This fork's posture*: internal use only within Asymbl. Forge is
   not offered as a service to external parties. Compliant with §1.a.

2. Logo / copyright restriction (§1.b):
   Cannot remove or modify the Multica LOGO or copyright information
   in the frontend (apps/web/).

   *This fork's posture*: the logo has been replaced with the Asymbl
   brand mark for internal team identification. This is a known
   deviation from the upstream license. Risk acknowledged by the
   stakeholder (Asymbl) for internal-only use.

   Mitigations:
   - Forge is never exposed to non-Asymbl users
   - Forge is never offered as a service or SaaS to anyone
   - Multica's copyright text in source files is preserved
   - If Multica's commercial team objects, the Multica logo will be
     re-applied immediately and a commercial license negotiated

Asymbl-specific changes
-----------------------
The diff between upstream Multica and this fork consists of:

- Brand replacement (logo, color palette, name strings) — internal only
- Email domain restriction middleware (gate signup to @asymbl.com)
- Email template polish (Asymbl branding)
- Renamed CLI binary (`forge` instead of `multica`)
- Mac desktop app rebrand (`com.asymbl.forge` bundle ID)
- Custom Docker image names and Compose configuration

All Asymbl-authored modifications inherit Apache License 2.0 terms.

